# Plan Documents in Workspace

All plan documents must be created and updated **inside the workspace** so they are versioned and visible in the project.

**Canonical location:** `plans/` (at the workspace root).

**Filename convention:** Use kebab-case based on the plan title (e.g. `plans-in-workspace.md`, `safe-retracts-option.md`).

## When creating a new plan

- Write the plan content to a file in `plans/<short-name>.md` using the **Write** tool.
- Use a short kebab-case name derived from the plan title. This ensures the canonical copy lives in the repo in addition to any plan created via the CreatePlan tool.

## When updating a plan

- Read and edit the plan file in `plans/` so the canonical copy stays in the workspace.
- Do not rely only on plan files stored outside the workspace (e.g. in Cursor’s default plan storage).
